message.entry: A column-wise comparison is not possible with a row vector input.
A row-wise comparison is not possible with a column vector input.
When one of the inputs is logical, the other input must be binary valued.
When one of the inputs is logical, number of bits, K, must be 1.
Word length must be a scalar.
Word length must be a finite, real integer.
The specified word length is too short for the matrix elements.
Only string and numeric arguments are accepted.
Input row vector must contain as many elements as there are columns in the input matrix.
Input column vector must contain as many elements as there are rows in the input matrix.
Input matrices must be the same size.
